From 1de72e11d655d0c2e9de33c11aa4b291c951cd82 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Robert Lee <robert@alva.xyz>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 09:44:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(campaign-3.0): card chrome + halo via filter:blur
 (rounds 44-46.27)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

S1 floating card chrome — final state:
- 1px solid #e5e5ea border drawn via two-fill technique (outer rect
  1 logical px larger than inner white card, no canvas2D stroke)
- radius 5/6 corners (small enough that corner AA mismatch with
  straight edges falls under visual detection threshold)
- Soft halo via direct ctx.filter='blur(10px)' on a #c8c8cd rect
  fill, drawn UNDER the sharp border. Color stays close enough to
  the border that bilinear sampling at the border->halo transition
  doesn't produce visible dark intermediates. Avoids canvas2D's
  shadowColor+shadowBlur API which exhibited asymmetric darkness
  through the WebGL pipeline (verified via pixel probe — same
  pattern across canvas2D shadow, offscreen-blur drawImage, and
  direct filter:blur on fill, indicating WebGL plane sampling
  bias under sub-pixel rasterization rather than a canvas issue;
  the visible halo is still uniform by eye)
- material.premultipliedAlpha=true so scene->RT blend preserves
  straight-alpha values, mix() composite in post shader resolves
  cleanly at the alpha edge
- Plane positions snapped to integer device pixels
- CA strength bumped 0.005 -> 0.020 (4x) so chromatic aberration
  reads clearly across card boundaries and headline text strokes
- Film grain gated by smoothstep(0.15, 1.0, r^2) — center clean,
  only section corners get the noise

S1 lens load race fix:
- THREE.js moved to deferred dynamic script tag by parallel task;
  inline lens IIFE was bailing out before THREE loaded. Replaced
  hard 'if (typeof THREE === undefined) return' with polling
  waitForThree(initLens) + 10s ceiling.

Mobile parity (<=760px):
- Phone media block restructured by section (nav / S1 / S2 / S3 /
  S4 / footer / modals)
- S3 leaderboard table: new 4-col grid (22 / 1fr / 58 / 52) so
  ROI + Risk pills no longer clip at 390px; .who wrapper div gets
  min-width:0 / flex:1 / overflow:hidden so name + handle actually
  ellipsize
- S2 stage marquee: desktop's 1250px backdrop-blur mask used to
  dim the entire phone viewport; on mobile the overlay is in
  normal flow with no mask and stage resets from flex to block
- S1 hero: H1 halo retuned for narrow viewport, tweet density
  dropped to 4, WebGL lens pass skipped entirely (battery + the
  visual payoff disappears at phone widths)
- S4 carousel cards reflow to calc(100vw - 56px)
- Modals: tight padding, full-width primary + ghost CTAs
- New 380px sub-breakpoint for iPhone SE-class screens
