+       2. Drop the tab affordance entirely — no left-rail title list, no
+          active-state highlight. Each entry becomes a self-contained
+          mini-card: cover (full-bleed) → title → body → CTA, stacked.
+       3. Section bleeds edge-to-edge horizontally. Section head + body
+          text keep their own 18 px inner padding for readability;
+          covers run flush with viewport edges.
+       4. The covers themselves live in `.agents-cards-stage` in the
+          DOM. We CLONE each cover into its matching `.agents-tab-item`
+          via JS (see setupAgentsMobile) on mount, so the cover sits
+          on top of its description. Original covers stay in the stage
+          for desktop; the stage itself is hidden on mobile. */
+
+    .agents-pin-section { height: auto; padding: 48px 0; }
